                        USE OF COOKIES
                    A cookie is a small data file that certain websites write to your hard drive when you visit them.
                    A cookie file can contain information such as a user ID that the site uses to track the pages
                    you’ve visited, but the only personal information a cookie can contain is information
                    you supply yourself. A cookie cannot read data off your hard disk or read cookie files created
                    by other sites. When accessing information stored in a database format, a basic version of cookies
                    is used to transfer an answer to the user who has initiated a question.

                    Nowhere on the Telindus site however are cookies being used that store specific information
                    on the user or surfer. Cookies on the Telindus site serve a more functional purpose i.e.
                    they are generated by an IIS web server (Internet Information Server), stored in the memory
                    of the browser implicating they disappear once the browser session has been terminated.

                        LINKS TO EXTERNAL SITES
                    Telindus web sites may contain links to external sites. Telindus is not responsible for the content
                    and the privacy practices of other web sites, and encourages you to examine each site’s privacy
                    policy and disclaimers in order to make your own decisions regarding the accuracy, reliability
                    and correctness of material and information found there.

                        APPLICATIONS, SURVEYS, REGISTRATION FORMS
                    Telindus has to collect certain information in order to be able to provide all requested services.
                    Compulsory indications will be expressly highlighted in applications, surveys, registration forms…
                </pre>
